				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>20 Dec 1869</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I have omitted nothing several of your <add>&#63;</add><lb/> but all have come duly to hand with the Occidents the last of wh<add>&#63;</add> were<lb/> received on the <date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> You will notice a very reasonable <add>&#63;</add> made<lb/> by the Express of only 1&#47;10 per package.  I <add>&#63;</add> a statement of <add>&#63;</add><lb/> &#38; disbursements showing a small Balance due you.  The arrear <add>&#63;</add><lb/> made every effort to collect but with little success.  <persName>Mr Goodman</persName> <add>&#63;</add><lb/> yet insists on not paying.  Several I do not ask for prompt <add>&#63;</add>ment<lb/> from&#8212;as they would willingly give up their subscriptions.  I will<add>&#63;</add> remit<lb/> the Balance due you&#8212;so soon as I ascertain if any thing has been <add>&#63;</add> reud<add>&#63;</add><lb/> to you in <placeName>Phila.</placeName>  We have now snow &#38; cold but no Ice&#8212;tho we <add>&#63;</add> soon<lb/> to have some.  The season has been mild &#38; favorable.  By the <add>&#63;</add> if<lb/> Railroad we are less distant than ever from <placeName>New York</placeName> this winter the<lb/> trip from <placeName>N York</placeName> to <placeName>Washington</placeName> is now made in 24 hours&#8212;<add>&#63;</add> in 12<lb/> hours so we are certain 2 to 2 &#189; days travel <add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I regret to hear a few differences between yourself &#38; <add>&#63;</add><lb/> congregations&#8212;there is yet time for an agreement<add>&#63;</add><lb/> satisfactory to all parties.  It would be unfortunate if <add>&#63;</add><lb/> work that is considered useful to all should prove <add>&#63;</add><lb/> <add>&#63;</add> alone&#8212;to harvesting to <persName>Mr Aaron Hart</persName> shall <add>&#63;</add> your<lb/> kind remembrance of her&#8212;they are in <placeName>Three Rivers</placeName>.  I<add>&#63;</add><lb/> the family entitled to the obituary notice in the last Oc<add>cident</add> they<lb/> may be readers but none of them are supporters thereof.  <add>&#63;</add> have<lb/> little regard for their principles and only by the <add>&#63;</add><lb/> are they ever well treated.  <persName>Mr Desola</persName> appears well <add>&#63;</add><lb/> here&#8212;he is certainly much liked and I believe <add>&#63;</add><lb/> few minutes can manage to give benevolent <add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mrs. Joseph</persName> &#38; child are well.  <persName>Miss Rebecca</persName> <add>&#63;</add><lb/> a <add>&#63;</add> convenient <sic>traveller</sic> when required to vis<add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mrs Joseph</persName> desires best regards   Believe me</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Truly <add>&#63;</add></p>
